# This file defines the required environment variable keys for this project.
#
# ⚠️ IMPORTANT:
# - DO NOT put any real values, credentials, secrets, or defaults here.
# - Only declare variable names (e.g., MY_KEY=).
#
# Purpose:
# - Used for validation when `safe: true` is set in Webpack dotenv plugin.
#   Check: https://www.npmjs.com/package/dotenv-webpack
# - Ensures all required variables are defined during build and runtime.
#
# Actual values are provided by (in order of priority):
# 1. .env.defaults (default values)
# 2. .env (local developer-specific values)
# 3. Direct environment variables (e.g., from CI/CD pipelines)
#
# Never commit actual secret values to any public or shared repository.

